Given these two files compiled as a static library and then linked into `main.cpp`, what does the following program print?

```cpp
// mathutils.h
int add(int a, int b);

// main.cpp
#include <iostream>
#include "mathutils.h"
int main() {
    std::cout << add(10, 32) << '\n';
}

// mathutils.cpp (archived into libmathutils.a)
int add(int a, int b) { return a + b; }
```
